# This repo tracks the composites web applications only.
#
# The git root is SN6 Resources/ rather than "03 Work Orders/" because the
# scripts in tools/ resolve their paths as  <tools>/../03 Work Orders/... , so
# they only run correctly from here. Keeping the root one level up means the
# tests and generators work unmodified instead of living as patched copies.
#
# The document side of SN6 Resources (pain points, standards, datasheets,
# printables, agent definition) stays local. Note that the datasheets and
# standards the app itself serves are already tracked, under
# "03 Work Orders/app/docs/".

# Ignore everything at the repo root...
/*

# ...then re-include the application and its tooling.
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/03 Work Orders/
!/tools/

# Never track these, at any depth:
.DS_Store
.venv/
node_modules/
.firebase/
